The paper discusses binary code similarity approaches for applications such as patch analysis, bug search, and malware detection and analysis, which are all related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation and evaluation of these approaches, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY) due to the use of benchmarks and methodologies for evaluation.
